# Correlation and Mutual Information | MATLAB

This project explores statistical correlation, mutual information, and classification performance using MATLAB. The goal was to analyze whether measurement features were Gaussian, determine how different feature sets affected classification error, and evaluate whether feature correlation or mutual information could influence model performance.

## Project Overview

Real-world datasets often contain features that are not statistically independent. These features may be correlated or may share mutual information, which can cause classifiers to over-count similar information and affect prediction performance.

This project investigated:

- Whether a measurement feature follows a Gaussian distribution
- Bayes classification error using individual measurement features
- Bayes classification error using all available features
- The effect of data normalization
- Neural network classification performance
- Statistical correlation between measurement features
- Differences between correlation and mutual information

